As per [https://moodle.org/mod/forum/discuss.php?d=319464#p1282517 this thread], the quiz activity on moodle can be made to look much nicer with some simple CSS changes.  The following changes are adapted from those by Phuong Hoang, with additional changes to match the campus theme.  Add this CSS to the main theme CSS.

To do: test how does this look with the mobile theme?

<pre>
/* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
 * Quiz beautification thanks to Phuong Hoang
 * https://moodle.org/mod/forum/discuss.php?d=319464#p1282517
 * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * */

.que .info > div {
    margin-left: 1.5em;
    /* margin-right: 15px; */
    display: inline;
    color: #fff;
}

.que .content {
    margin: 0 0 0 0;
    width: auto;
}

.que .info {
    float: none;
    width: auto;
    background-color: #000;
    border: 1px solid #000;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: -5px;
    padding: 8px;
    color: #fff;
}

.que h3.no {
    display: inline;
    font-size: 1.5em;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-left: 10px;
    color: #fff;
}

.que span.qno {
    font-size: 1em;
}

.que .formulation {
    background-color: #fff;
    border-color: #000;
}

/* end of quiz beautification */
</pre>

