[[Category:Core_Code_Changes]]

This change was made in order to automatically display a user's portfolio image in their profile on [[Moodle]].

== Simple HTML link ==

In 'user/profile.php', add the following around line 249 (line 275 in 2.7, immediately after <code>echo html_writer::start_tag('dl', array('class' => 'list'));</code> )

<pre>
if ($DB->record_exists('portfolio_instance_user', array('userid' => $user->id,'name' => 'nsid'))){
	$flickrID = $DB->get_record('portfolio_instance_user', array('userid' => $userid,'name' => 'nsid'), 'value', $strictness=IGNORE_MISSING);

	if ($flickrID->value) {
		$flickrUrl = "https://www.flickr.com/photos/$flickrID->value";

		echo html_writer::tag('dt', get_string('portfolio', 'core_portfolio'));
		echo html_writer::tag('dd', html_writer::link($flickrUrl, s($flickrUrl)));
	}
}</pre>

If the student has linked a portfolio to Moodle, there will be several lines created on the database table <code>portfolio_instance_user</code>.  This code checks for these lines and, if found, adds them on the profile page.  There is an additional check to make sure that the 'value' variable is not blank (which may happen if a user's profile has been [[Manually_Delete_User_Profiles|manually deleted]]).  It will display something like:

<blockquote>'''Portfolio'''    https://www.flickr.com/photos/123665615@N06</blockquote>

== Advanced Link with Message ==

If, rather than a link, you want to display a translatable message and icon for the portfolio to appear on the user page, replace the above code with this instead:

<pre>
if ($DB->record_exists('portfolio_instance_user', array('userid' => $user->id,'name' => 'nsid'))){
	$flickrID = $DB->get_record('portfolio_instance_user', array('userid' => $userid,'name' => 'nsid'), 'value', $strictness=IGNORE_MISSING);

	if ($flickrID->value) {
		$flickrUrl = "https://www.flickr.com/photos/$flickrID->value";

		$iconurl = new moodle_url('/pix/t/portfolioadd.png');
		$statusicon = html_writer::tag('img', '', array('src'=>$iconurl, 'class'=>'icon icon-post', 'alt'=>'Flickr'));
		echo html_writer::tag('dt', get_string('portfolio', 'core_portfolio'));
		echo html_writer::tag('dd', html_writer::link($flickrUrl, s(get_string('viewuserportfolio', 'theme_essential', $user->firstname)).$statusicon));
	}
}
</pre>

This code is using the same picture that appears next to images prompting users to upload (we [[Change_Portfolio_Upload_Thumbnail|changed that to a Flickr logo elsewhere]]).  Instead of displaying text, it is actually searching for a custom string in the language file (notice that it also uses the user's first name as a variable when calling this string).  Thus, you will also need to append the following to the end of each of the [[Customize_Language_Files|language files]] in the main Escoffier theme (translated as appropriate):

<code>$string['viewuserportfolio'] = 'View {$a}\'s Portfolio';</code>

The {$a} in the code will display as the user's first name in their profile.  It will end up looking something like this:

<blockquote>'''Portfolio'''    [https://www.flickr.com/photos/123665615@N06 View Sally's Portfolio]</blockquote>

