We re-purposed the Choice activity in Moodle to act as out "Start Course"; this is where the student reaffirms their enrollment agreement before starting the major course activities. Therefore, students don't need to enter this activity after making a choice, and after the student makes a choice, it is not obvious how to return to their course.  Therefore, we added some code to redirect the user after they make a choice.

In "/mod/choice/view.php", add the following code (this should be able to go anywhere in the file, as long it is '''ABOVE''' the last line, '''<code>echo $OUTPUT->footer();</code>'''; if placed earlier, may need to initialize and check $current):

<pre>
if ($current) {
    $back_url = new moodle_url('/course/view.php', array('id'=>$course->id));
    redirect($back_url);
}
</pre>

To initialize $current, you'll have to add some code before the if statement:

<pre>
$current = false;
$current = $DB->get_record('choice_answers', array('choiceid' => $choice->id, 'userid' => $USER->id));
</pre>

== Limit Redirect to Single Option Choices ==

To keep the versatility of the Choice activity, you can add some additional code to check that '''a)''' this choice activity cannot be updated and '''b)''' this choice activity has only one option.

<pre>
$options = choice_prepare_options($choice, $USER, $cm, $allresponses);
$total_options = count($options['options']);
if ($current && !$choice->allowupdate && $total_options<2) {
	$back_url = new moodle_url('/course/view.php', array('id'=>$course->id));
	redirect($back_url);
}
</pre>

Note that $current must still be initialized depending on where in the file you place this code.

