When you look up a user from the Quickfind List (aka All Users List) in a course that the user is not enrolled in, you'll simply get an error message with the option to continue back to the course.  In most cases, what we'd rather do is go to the user's sitewide profile, so let's adda redirect.

In /user/view.php around line 133, you'll see the following code:

<pre>
    if (!is_enrolled($coursecontext, $user->id)) {
        // TODO: the only potential problem is that managers and inspectors might post in forum, but the link
        //       to profile would not work - maybe a new capability - moodle/user:freely_acessile_profile_for_anybody
        //       or test for course:inspect capability.
        if (has_capability('moodle/role:assign', $coursecontext)) {
            $PAGE->navbar->add($fullname);
            echo $OUTPUT->header();
            echo $OUTPUT->heading(get_string('notenrolled', '', $fullname));
        } else {
            echo $OUTPUT->header();
            $PAGE->navbar->add($struser);
            echo $OUTPUT->heading(get_string('notenrolledprofile'));
        }
        if (!empty($_SERVER['HTTP_REFERER'])) {
            echo $OUTPUT->continue_button($_SERVER['HTTP_REFERER']);
        }
        echo $OUTPUT->footer();
        exit;
    }
</pre>

Near the end of all this, immediately before the footer is echoed, add this line:

<pre>
redirect(new moodle_url('/user/view.php', array('id'=>$user->id)));
</pre>

