== Excel Dates ==

By default, the activity completion report gives completion dates in a text format that is not readable by excel, so we'll change the way these dates are passes.

Open /report/progress/index.php, and around line 372 you should see: 

<pre>
$date=userdate($thisprogress->timemodified);
</pre>

This is fine in the html preview, but bad for our excel file, so we'll surround it with an if statement:

<pre>
if (!$csv) {
	$date=userdate($thisprogress->timemodified);
}
</pre>

The $csv variable tracks whether this is being downloaded or viewed in browser.  We need another statement if $csv is true:

<pre>
if (!$csv) {
	$date=userdate($thisprogress->timemodified);
} else {
	$date = (usertime($thisprogress->timemodified) / 86400) + 25569;
}
</pre>

Because moodle timestamps count seconds and excel timestamps count days, we divide our time by the number of seconds in a day, 86,400.  Moodle timestamps count seconds since the unix epoch (1/1/1970), but excel counts days since 1/1/1900, so we'll also add the number of days between these two epochs, 25,569.

== Full Activity Names ==

This change can be done to match the completion report to the gradebook, which does not truncate names.  In the same file (), around line 320 you should see:

<pre>
$displayname = shorten_text($activity->name);
</pre>

Replace it with:

<pre>
if ($activity->modname == 'label') {
	$displayname = 'Label: '.shorten_text($activity->name); 
} elseif ($activity->modname == 'assign') {
	$displayname = 'Assignment: '.format_text($activity->name);
} else {
	$displayname = ucfirst($activity->modname).': '.format_text($activity->name);
}
</pre>

