If there are more than 5 unread messages, the message menu still only shows 5.  We want to fix this to show the correct number of messages, and add a link to view all unread if there are more than 5.

In <code>/theme/essential/renderers/core_renderer.php</code>, around line 441, you'll see the line:

<pre>
$messagelist['newmessages'] = count($messages);
</pre>

Delete or comment out that line and replace it with the following, taken from the <code>message_count_unread_messages</code> function in <code>/message/lib.php</code>:

<pre>
$messagelist['newmessages'] = $DB->count_records_select('message', "useridto = ?", array($USER->id), "COUNT('id')");
</pre>

Next, to add a link for more messages, you'll need to add some code in the same file.  From around line 384 to line 420, you'll see a long <code>foreach</code> loop (shortened here):

<pre>
            foreach ($messages['messages'] as $message) {
                $addclass = 'read';
                $iconadd = '-o';

                if ($message->unread) {
                    ...
                }

                $messagesubmenu->add($messagecontent, $message->url, $message->text);
            }
</pre>

After this <code>foreach</code> loop, and before the next ending bracket, add some code like this:

<pre>
	if ($messages['newmessages'] > $totalmessages) {
		$moretext = get_string('more', 'mod_data').' '.strtolower(get_string('unreadmessages', 'core_message', $messages['newmessages'] - $totalmessages));
		$morecontent = html_writer::start_div('notification unread');
		$morecontent .= html_writer::start_span('msg-body');
		$morecontent .= html_writer::span($moretext, 'msg-more');
		$morecontent .= html_writer::end_span();
		$morecontent .= html_writer::end_div();
		$moreurl = new moodle_url('/message/index.php', array('viewing' => 'recentnotifications'));
		$messagesubmenu->add($morecontent, $moreurl, $moretext);
	}
</pre>

