== '''THIS EDIT IS FOR MOODLE 2.5 ONLY''' ==

To remove the "Back to Top" feature, you'll need to edit the Essential theme layout pages.  Using FTP, navigate to /theme/essential/layout/" and you'll see several .php files.  Check each for the following code, which you can simply comment out with standard HTML:


<pre>
<script type="text/javascript">
 jQuery(document).ready(function() {
  var offset = 220;
  var duration = 500;
  jQuery(window).scroll(function() {
  if (jQuery(this).scrollTop() > offset) {
   jQuery('.back-to-top').fadeIn(duration);
  } else {
   jQuery('.back-to-top').fadeOut(duration);
  }
 });

 jQuery('.back-to-top').click(function(event) {
 event.preventDefault();
 jQuery('html, body').animate({scrollTop: 0}, duration);
 return false;
 })
});
</script>
</pre>

Note that this is only applicable for version 5 of the Essential theme.

[[Category:Outdated_Moodle_Changes]]

In order to display the courses how we wanted on the front page of moodle, we created a custom PHP script which is displayed in an iFrame.

As of 8/4/2014, the script has been modified so that it now displays all visible courses the user is currently enrolled in, sorted by category. It allows one level of subcategories, but will need to be modified to allow further levels.  Categories with subcategories are displayed first (ie Culinary Program divided into Culinary Basics, Groundwork, etc).  Categories without subcategories are grouped together at the end.

If the user is an admin, the script will show all available courses.

As of this edit, all you need to do to add items to the front page display is to add categories and courses as you want them to appear.  The script is based on "sortorder", so you can order categories and courses however you like (with the caveats that ALL categories with subcategories will be displayed before categories without, and if a category contains both subcategories and courses in the top level category, those in the top level category will be displayed last).  The course full name (or short name on mobile), overview file, and truncated summary will be displayed, if available.

There is an additional piece of code that hides certain, preset categories, identified by category id. As of this writing, the categories "Full Programs" (id=1) and "Resources" (id=4) are completely hidden from the course display. To add or remove categories from this list, you will need to edit the array variable <code>$lolCats</code> around line 36.

