[[Category:Outdated_Moodle_Changes]]

'''''This change is made obsolete by [[Show_Contents_by_Default_on_Vertical_Phone]]'''''

In the mobile Snap Theme, when you enter a course with the "collapsible topics" layout holding the phone vertically (portrait mode), the table of contents does not display and it is not immediately apparent what to do as a student.  Therefore, we want to add a message that displays only when the phone is vertical.

First, we'll add our message in the Snap Theme's language file, /theme/snap/lang/en/theme_snap.php  At the end of the file (but without leaving spaces), add:

<pre>
$string['vertical-phone'] = 'Please turn your device sideways to view course contents.';
</pre>

Next, we need to show this string somewhere that will display when the contents are hidden.  Open /course/format/topcoll/renderer.php  From around line 562 to 565, you'll see the following code:

<pre>
if ($this->tcsettings['displayinstructions'] == 2) {
    // Collapsed Topics instructions.
    echo $this->display_instructions();
}
</pre>

Immediately after, add another 'if' statement:

<pre>
if ($this->mobiletheme === true) {
	echo html_writer::tag('p', get_string('vertical-phone', 'theme_snap'), array('class' => 'topcoll-display-instructions vertical', 'style' => 'font-style: oblique;'));
}
</pre>

Make sure the name of the string and the file in the 'get_string()' function are correct.

If we stopped here, the message would display on any mobile theme, regardless of the phone's orientation.  To fix this, we'll add custom CSS to the Snap Theme using one of the classes we assigned to the paragraph tag above, 'vertical':

<pre>
@media only screen and (orientation: landscape) {
      .vertical {
            display: none;
      }
}
</pre>

Now, when the phone is held horizontally (in landscape mode), the message will not display.

