We edited the online users block to display larger user pictures and to display an employee role, if applicable.

== Moodle 2.7 ==

In this version, the picture size is controlled by the class, "userpicture", so changing the size in the code here does nothing.  However, the default size is now 35 pixels, so this change is not longer necessary.

Adding the $employee_role variable can be done in the same manner as before, just take note that now you'll insert it somewhere around line 184.

If you want to modify the colored border around the picture, you will need to modify the class "userpicture".  If you would like to vary the border based on some variable, you will need to make new classes for each variation, along with some changes to the PHP code.  Before the line containing <code>$OUTPUT->user_picture</code> (line 184 before edits) you will declare a new variable:

<pre>$user_pic_class = 'userpicture';</pre>

This way, the picture will inherit the normal class in lieu of other changes.  Next, add if statements to check whatever variables you wish and change the new variable to match one of your custom classes.  Finally, change this section of the code:

<pre>array('size'=>16, 'alttext'=>false, 'link'=>false)</pre>

To this:

<pre>array('size'=>16, 'alttext'=>false, 'link'=>false, 'class'=>$user_pic_class)</pre>

