== Moodle 2.7 ==

[[Category:Moodle_2.7]]

This has drastically changed as of Moodle 2.7. In 'theme/essential/renderers/core_renderer.php', around line 597, you'll see the comment::

<pre>// Start dropdown menu items</pre>

After this, the different menu items are created by a series of if statements.  Most of the individual items are marked by a comment, so you can pretty easily place new menu items as you wish.

We'll add the new "My Account" menu item after "Badges" but before "Logout".  Around line 688, we'll place this code:

<pre>
	// Check if user has WooCommerce id
	$WCid = $DB->get_record('user_info_data', array('userid'=>$USER->id, 'fieldid'=>'3'))->data;
        if ($WCid) {
            $branchlabel = '<em><i class="fa fa-credit-card"></i>' . get_string('myaccount', 'theme_essential') . '</em>';
            $branchurl = new moodle_url('/escoffierfiles/myaccountredirect.php');
            $usermenu .= html_writer::tag('li', html_writer::link($branchurl, $branchlabel));

	    $usermenu .= html_writer::empty_tag('hr', array('class' => 'sep'));
	}
</pre>

* The first line is just a comment to let us know what this menu item is.
* The second line creates a variable of the WCid by checking the custom fields table.  Ensure you are looking for the correct custom field, based on the 'fieldid'.
* The third line checks if the WCid exists (or, more specifically, is a non-zero value).
* The fourth line create the text that will display, including a FontAwesome icon.
* The fifth line establishes the URL that this menu item will link to, in this case the [[Create_Account_Redirect_Page|account redirect page]] we created.
* The sixth line actually renders the previous two lines.
* The seventh line is blank.
* The eighth line create a line separator, so this menu item will appear in its own sub-section.

Afterwards, you can add the following to create menu items for teachers and managers. Teachers get a link to the user index, managers get this plus a link to the course index:

<pre>
	//Render admin options
	$adminoptions = FALSE;
	if (has_capability('moodle/user:viewhiddendetails', $context)){
		$branchlabel = '<em><i class="fa fa-users"></i>' . get_string('userindex', 'theme_essential') . '</em>';
		$branchurl = new moodle_url('/user/index.php?id='.$course->id);
		$usermenu .= html_writer::tag('li', html_writer::link($branchurl, $branchlabel));
		$adminoptions = TRUE;
	}	
	if (has_capability('moodle/course:viewhiddencourses', $context) || has_capability('moodle/site:uploadusers', $context)){
		$branchlabel = '<em><i class="fa fa-sitemap"></i>' . get_string('courseindex', 'theme_essential') . '</em>';
		$branchurl = new moodle_url('/course/index.php');
		$usermenu .= html_writer::tag('li', html_writer::link($branchurl, $branchlabel));
		$adminoptions = TRUE;
	}
	if ($adminoptions){
		$usermenu .= html_writer::empty_tag('hr', array('class' => 'sep'));
	}
</pre>

==Moodle 2.5 ==

The file 'theme/essential/renderers/core_renderer.php' has been edited quite a bit to customize the menu, so rather than noting the changes individually, I'll be adding in the large piece of code to date that has been added/changed. This will all go around line 147, between the code for the "badges" menu item and "logout":

<pre>
//$branch->add('<em><i class="icon-file"></i>'.get_string('privatefiles', 'block_private_files').'</em>',new moodle_url('/user/files.php'),get_string('privatefiles', 'block_private_files'));
//tk adding 'My Grades' link
global $COURSE, $USER;
$branch->add('<em><i class="icon-check"></i>My Grades</em>',new moodle_url('/grade/report/user/index.php?id='.$COURSE->id),'My Grades');
//tk adding 'My Account' link
$branch->add('<em><i class="icon-credit-card"></i>My Account</em>',new moodle_url('/escoffierfiles/myaccountredirect.php'),'My Account');
//tk adding section for Admin / Teacher links
//global $COURSE, $USER; <-- this was added above for 'My Grades', no longer needed here
$context = get_context_instance(CONTEXT_COURSE, $COURSE->id, true);
$roles = get_user_roles($context, $USER->id, true);
$permitted_roles = array(1,3,4,9,10); //correspond to manager, editingteacher, teacher, supervisor, chefmentor
$user_view = FALSE;
if (is_siteadmin()) {
  $user_view = TRUE;
} else {
  foreach ($roles as $role) {
    if (in_array($role->roleid, $permitted_roles)) {
      $user_view = TRUE;
      break;
    }
  }
}
if ($user_view) {
  //tk adding 'User Index' link
  $branch->add('<em><i class="icon-group"></i>User Index</em>',new moodle_url('/user/index.php?id='.$COURSE->id),'User Index');
  //tk adding 'Course Index' link
  $branch->add('<em><i class="icon-sitemap"></i>Course Index</em>',new moodle_url('/course/index.php'),'Course Index');
}
//tk end</pre>

Note that this adds a link for the account redirect, but you also need to [[Create_Account_Redirect_Page|create that page]].
